#################################################################################
#  README
#  ======
#
#
#  This suite of scripts provides a basic configuration for emacs v24 on
#    Arch linux.  The root emacs file, ~/.emacs calls several additional files
#    that include themes, formatting, hotkeys, the repository info for installs
#    and upgrades, various hooks for different editing modes and a file that
#    has provides nice modeline formatting (I can't find where I got the original
#    file).
#
#
#  FILES:
#    .emacs
#        custom.el
#        my-packages.el
#        my-modes.el
#        my-modeline.el
#
#
#  ARCH DEPENDENCIES:  emacs 24.5-2
#
#
#  USE:  Place .emacs in your home directory (~/)
#        Place dependencies in ~/.emacs.d/
#
#  NB:  If something goes wonky with one of the files or future customizations,
#         use the debug mode to debug the (e.g. .emacs) file
#
#       $ emacs ~/.emacs --debug-init
#
#
#  TODOs:
#################################################################################
